commitResults.messageBody:
main() was overloaded so executeCommand() was created to house the
main command execution code in its own function. This reduces bloat
in main() and makes the code more readable.

commitResults.messageBody:
toString() in Task.java produced a string that was hard to parse
back into a task object. A new function was needed to produce a
string that could be easily parsed to create a Task object.

commitResults.messageTitle: Task.java: Add getStatusInt()
commitResults.messageBody:
Moved the conversion for the isDone field into an int into its own
getStatusInt() function so that subclasses can call it for their own
overridden toSaveString() method and not repeat code.
